column5: Are there any Lac Seul predictions on Ice out and water levels this spring?
Prov 1800 will keep an eye on it for everyone!

Here's a website from Sioux Lookout. If you look at the Live Webcam, there's a barrel out on the ice just to the right of the grill and just above the deck railing. Click on Overview and you can see the dates of the barrel sinking in past years. http://endofwinter.ca

My first guide day is on Lac Suel May 22 out of Onaway.Will see how far i get.Normally like to with east in McKenzie or broad and sunlight as east shore warms up the most and lot of spawning fish head to the warm water.Normally can be 10 degrees difference from east shore to west shore.
